  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to know the reason for messages not arriving.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Any individual mail server is currently not High Availability, which means that if it goes down messages aren't received. We want to have some kind of visual indicator, such as a shaded topbar or a green/red light in mail server settings that indicate that connection has been broken. A simple ping to the mailserver should suffice.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, indicate when no peers are connected (`admin.peers` or so).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nGet visual feedback if mail server is down.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo visual feedback.",
